            "abstractNote": "Of the 10 recognized species in the genus Micronycteris, seven species (brachyotis, daviesi, hirsuta, megalotis, minuta, nicefori, and sylvestris) have been reported to occur in Suriname. Micronycteris daviesi is easily distinguished from the other species by its large size (forearm over 50 mm) and massive dentition. The next largest species (forearm over 43 mm)—M. hirsuta—\\s distinguished by having the upper inner incisors separated at the base but in contact at the tip and having lower incisors that are high and wedged between canines so that the canines are in contact behind the incisors.",
